title: S-D-A cross country qualifies team, individuals
text: S-D-A cross country qualifies team, individuals Comment Nebraska City News-Press - Nebraska City, NE Writer Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 11:31 AM Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 11:31 AM The Syracuse-Dunbar-Avoca boys’ cross country team qualified for state and three Rocket girls qualified as individuals during district action at Boys Town on Thursday. Keegan Pope was the top runner for the S-D-A boys’ team, which scored 26 points and finished at the top of an eight-team field. Qualifying for the Rocket girls’ team were Kim Lowman, Emma Porter, and Kayla Arnold. The top 15 individuals and top three teams qualified for the state meet, which will be Friday, Oct. 23, at Kearney. See a story about the district meet and a salute to the S-D-A qualifiers in the Thursday, Oct. 22, Journal-Democrat. Nebraska City News-Press - Nebraska City, NE Writer
